fields.name: books+experiments
fields.description: Our books+experiments section is a collection of commercial and experimental books and other print items that we have collaborated on with poets, writers, and artists over the past few years.

fields.name: print
fields.description: We have extensive knowledge and expertise in multiple print media. Our print work ranges from small-scale brochures, accordian books, custom-designed cases, to large-scale annual reports, posters, and bus panels.

fields.name: signage
fields.description: In this section, you can browse through museum exhibit panels, storefront concepts, and design-wrapped cars. We have often continued our work into this realm because of previous relationships with clients who have specific signage requests.

fields.name: web
fields.description: We follow strong design principles and thought while approaching the continously-expanding and technologically-evolving world of website design. This can be seen through our approaches to structure, color systems, architectural and navigational options, and the incorporation of narratives/layers of heirarchical content present and available in our designs.

fields.name: identity
fields.description: We have done branding for a number of our clients, that range from the small business enterprenuer, to the arts/cultural organization to the eco-friendly non-profit. Our process for branding and identity development begin with comparative visuals audits for each of our clients, which inform our logo and visual explorations.

fields.name: Sandpaper/Sunlight
fields.description: This book of poetry is a collaboration between a designer, an artist, and a poet.

fields.name: Fragments of This Mind
fields.description: A collection of poetry, prose, reality, and fiction by author Raman Prasad.

fields.name: The Moti Stories
fields.description: Excerpts from short stories centered around the adventures of Moti (a dog). Targeted towards children with dyslexia and reading disabilities, these stories are produced in collaboration with a renowned Mumbai-based child psychologist.

fields.name: Garden Prose
fields.description: Excerpts from a poetry book.

fields.name: Travelling Texts
fields.description: This book was written and designed to explore space, place, and identity issues.

fields.name: Bad Ass Woman Chronicles
fields.description: A dialogue between the written and the visual. This collection of shorts and stories is centered around the female as mystical, revengeful, compassionate, thoughtful, and powerful. In collaboration with author Chandra Prasad.

fields.name: EA Innotown
fields.description: Design for a interactive presentation for Elias Arts, a NYC-based sound design company, to be presented by the then CEO and founder Scott Elias, at Innotown, a Norwegian business conference.

fields.name: EA Interactive
fields.description: Design of a multi-purpose interactive presentation for Elias Arts, a NYC-based sound design company.

fields.name: EA Present
fields.description: We helped Elias Arts design a format for use in their in-house powerpoint presentations. The design needed to reflect the unique spirit of this innovative music company but also communicate specific information.

fields.name: Center for International & Area Studies
fields.description: We designed a promotional viewbook for the Center for International and Area Studies at Yale University. This Center encompasses programs from across the globe, including Asia, Africa, and South America.

fields.name: Felucca Films
fields.description: We developed the visual identity for a film production company, with a focus on issues in Egypt and the Middle East.

fields.name: Museum of the Moving Image
fields.description: Worked on the design of Behind the Screen, an internationally traveling exhibition for the Museum of the Moving Image. This project consisted of over 70 pieces of illuminated print signage and 20 digital interfaces for interactive multimedia experiences — that ranged from special effects to animation to the history of the moving image. It was translated into three languages.

fields.name: Langston Hughes at 100
fields.description: This multimedia exhibition contains photos, songs, videos, and other unique elements from Langston Hughes' life as a poet, observer, and artist. Most of these elements would not have been available in a typical physical exhibit, and the challenge in this project was to seamlessly flow these different items into a unique yet legible design system.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: SCD Website
fields.description: Since 2000, Nymdesign has worked collaboratively with SCD Recipe, to create the online identity of this recipe-based website. The design uses turn-of-the-century illustrations to identify the various food categories.

fields.name: EA IDSA
fields.description: Art-directed a multimedia presentation for a conference sponsored by the Industrial Designers Society of America (IDSA).

fields.name: Bring It On Travel
fields.description: Designed the online identity for Bring It On, a travel firm that specializes in customized tour packages.

fields.name: Yale University Library
fields.description: We have worked with the Yale Library system for over 10 years to create custom-based web templates for their main "front door" site, as well as for smaller collections and libraries across the university. These have included the Faber Birren Collection of Books on Color, Manuscripts & Archives, and Digital Collections, among others.

fields.name: Yale World Fellows Program
fields.description: We collaborated on the design of the Yale World Fellows Program, that invites promising individuals across the globe to come and spend one year at the university. This prestigious program needed to have an online presence that was global, modern, and visually legible across languages and nationalities. Created with AHDesign.

fields.name: Swallow Gallery
fields.description: We designed the website for Swallow Gallery, an eclectic art gallery based in Brooklyn that showcases glass and ceramic pieces.

fields.name: F Train
fields.description: Spreads from a book about travelling the New York City subway's F Train.

fields.name: Our Conversations, Uncontested
fields.description: These pages are the visual interpretation of a poem written by Francesco Fiondella.

fields.name: Walking
fields.description: A book re-interpreting movement through space and time.

fields.name: Birthday 90 Series
fields.description: A series of topic-specific cards designed to celebrate an important event.

fields.name: 9 1/2: A Journey of 40 Weeks
fields.description: A pregnancy book documenting each month leading to the final moment. It is a time-line project that takes us back into old family stories and anecdotes, but also forward into the emotions, actions, and anticipation of the soon-to-be parents.

fields.name: Adventures in the Family Kitchen
fields.description: Adventures is predominantly an Italian/Indian cookbook with recipes for the Specific Carbohydrate Diet. Each recipe is identified by place, chef's name, and quirky turn-of-the-century illustrations.

fields.name: Colitis & Me
fields.description: Spreads from the book Colitis & Me: A Story of Recovery written by author Raman Prasad. Each page of this non-fiction narrative is designed to support and enhance the reading experience through use of typography, movement, and visual cues.

fields.name: Deconstructing Passiac
fields.description: The left side of this experimental exercise zooms into a pixelated oblivion, while the right side becomes comprehensive and legible.

fields.name: Sun Rays
fields.description: A short story book of traveling planets and systems by Raman Prasad.

fields.name: Journeys
fields.description: Journeys was visualized as a typographic exercise that fuses three disparate writings to create a novel reading experience. The authors own narrative of exclusion and belonging, of home and lack thereof, of race and space identity is used to flow, interrupt, crash, and explode.

fields.name: Urban Landscapes
fields.description: Urban Landscapes takes a look at the way public space, identity, and community is divided. It offers design intervention as a way to create new conversations within this spectrum.

fields.name: Leroy Anderson Exhibition
fields.description: These panels are part of an exhibition to commemorate the composer Leroy Anderson on his birth centennial.

fields.name: Le Bon March
fields.description: Created design concepts for the facade/storefront of a gourmet grocery store.

fields.name: Yale Center for British Art
fields.description: Design-wrapped a car for the exhibition "The Art of Exploration" at the Yale Center for British Art.

fields.name: Bright Eyes
fields.description: Designed the storefront identity for New York-based Bright Eyes Optometry.

fields.name: 30 Cards / 30 Years
fields.description: A collection of 30 cards designed to commemorate 30 moments in an individuals life.

fields.name: 4 Saints 3 Acts
fields.description: The avant garde performance of Virgil Thompson and Gertrude Stein's "Four Saints in Three Acts" called for an innovative program design. The audience program was designed as a series of cards - they functioned independently and each had specific information, but when put together as a puzzle they created a larger message/image.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Foundations & Futures
fields.description: Designed materials for Foundations & Futures — a conference for Asian and Asian-American alumni at Yale University. The brochure integrated information about the actual event with Asian-inspired patterns, and a historical timeline of Asian students from the 1800's till the present.

fields.name: Connect With Yale
fields.description: Connect With Yale New Haven brought the successful "Connect" series launched by the Association of Yale Alumni in cities nationwide back to Yale itself. The day-long event included lectures, tours, and the opportunity to reconnect with one's alma mater once again.

fields.name: Day of Service
fields.description: The "Day of Service" series was first launched 3 years ago at the state level, and has now been taken to the global level. We designed the visual identity (logo), and all supporting materials such as postcards, brochures, and advertisements for this unique service event.

fields.name: Henry Roe Cloud Conference
fields.description: Designed the print and online materials for a conference focused on Native American issues at Yale.

fields.name: The Redpath Seminar
fields.description: For the past five years, we have designed the print and online identity for The Redpath Seminar. Each years' seminar has a different focus - ranging from contemporary culture to grand strategy to environmentalism. It brings this knowledge to an expanded audience across the country.

fields.name: Bollingen Prize for Poetry
fields.description: The Bollingen Prize for Poetry is awarded bi-annually to a prominent American poet since 19??. We designed the print identity for this program, including invites, posters, brochures, cd and video cases. \r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Core Radiance
fields.description: We designed the visual identity for Core Radiance, a wellness center based in northern Connecticut. The brochure was designed as a series of cards that could be distributed based on the clients needs.

fields.name: Yale Latino Alumni Reunion
fields.description: We designed the promotional materials for a Latino Alumni conference at Yale University.

fields.name: CREA
fields.description: Initial brochure concepts for CREA, a feminist human rights organization based in New Delhi.

fields.name: Connect With Yale National Series
fields.description: Designed brochure/s for the one-day event, Connect With Yale, that has taken place across various cities in North America. Each brochure follows a format, but is uniquely identified through use of specific colors and local historical maps.

fields.name: Connect New York Series
fields.description: We designed a series of outreach events for New York-based special identity groups. These print items were visually based on the Connect With Yale series, but were more specific to each identifying group (LGBTQ, Black, Asian, and Latino/a) through use of color and imagery.

fields.name: Desipina & Company
fields.description: Nymdesign has collaborated with Desipina & Co. since its founding to create all design materials for this Asian-fusion theatre company based in New York City. Items ranged from posters, postcards, and brochures, to magnets, tshirts, and stickers.

fields.name: Elias Arts
fields.description: Between 2001-2005, Nymdesign worked closely with Elias Arts on multiple projects ranging from company press kits to magazine advertisements to dvd/cd-mailers.

fields.name: Fleur de Sel Restaurant
fields.description: We created the designs for the menus and all other print materials for this Michelin-starred restaurant in New York City's Flatiron district. The menu case was designed to accommodate a fresh insert on a daily  basis. We also assisted with Fleur de Sel's venture "Leapfrog Caterers" that focused on bringing this style of modern French cooking into other spaces.

fields.name: Hiding Divya Film
fields.description: We worked closely with the director and producers of this film to create promotional postcards, eblasts, and other required design materials.

fields.name: Harvard Kennedy School
fields.description: We have worked with different departments and programs with the Harvard Kennedy School to create brochures, folders, stationery, and other items.

fields.name: Consortium for Energy Policy Research
fields.description: We have designed the 90-page annual report for the Consortium for Energy Policy Research at Harvard since 2008. The designed used color and images to identify each chapter ans allow the reader to browse easily through the abundant information.

fields.name: Juvenile Jurisprudence
fields.description: We designed the brochure, poster, postcard, and invites for the exhibition Juvenile Jurisprudence: Law and Children's Literature that was showing at the Beinecke Rare Book & Manuscript Library.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Langston Hughes
fields.description: Langston Hughes at 100 was an exhibition at the Beinecke Rare Book & Manuscript Library that celebrated the brith anniversary of this prominent African-American poet/artist. We designed the invites, posters, advertisements, and even bus panels relating to this exhibit. \r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Massachusetts Children's Alliance
fields.description: Nymdesign has worked with the Massachusetts Children's Alliance to create its visual identity across a range of print items: brochures in 8 languages, event cards, stickers, folders, etc. In addition to the logo and color system, we commisioned a local illustrator to create artwork that we could use across a variety of materials.

fields.name: Yale SOM
fields.description: We designed the Class of 2010 Admit book that is sent to prospective (accepted) students at the Yale School of Management. This book needed to integrate (objective) factual information with (subjective) anecdotes and stories/profiles. The challenge was to create a piece that enticed but also communicated effectively.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: UM
fields.description: Nymdesign branded UM Projects and created a system of identity and print materials for its usage.

fields.name: Visual Arts at Yale
fields.description: We created the identity for this conference aimed at connecting professionals in the arts. As the grid moved from page to page, so did the colors, and a historical timeline. \r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: William Walton: Faade
fields.description: Nymdesign worked on the program brochure and case for the music exhibit "Faade" at the Beinecke Rare Book & Manuscript Library.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Iriving S. Gilmore Music Library
fields.description: We have worked closely with the archivists/librarians at the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library to create appropriate materials for music-related exhibits (ranging from Mozart to Anderson) that they have curated over the past few years.

fields.name: Daniel Read: Sacred Music
fields.description: Designed exhibition materials for the exhibition "Daniel Read and the Flowering of Sacred Music in New Haven" at the Beinecke Rare Book & Manuscript Library. These included postcards, posters and an event brochure.

fields.name: Yale School of Public Health
fields.description: We worked on the design concept of the Yale Public Health - a magazine launched in Fall 2009. This 45-page magazine contained a variety of articles from full-length features to small tidbits of information. The challenge was to come up with a cohesive format that seamlessly connected all the content, but also visually seperated one story from the next. Created with AHDesign.

fields.name: United Nations Population Fund
fields.description: We worked with one of the UN agencies - the United Nations Population Fund (UNFPA) to create a series awareness brochures for fundraising, governmental, and field usage. They focused in range from HIV awareness to contraceptive procurement services.

fields.name: Invites
fields.description: We have designed cards for numerous weddings, bat-mitzvahs, births, anniversary celebrations, and more. We work closely with those involved in these important "life" events to come up with a very personalized creative solution.

fields.name: Aangan India
fields.description: Designed the website for the non-profit, Aangan, based in Mumbai. This non-profit aims to create a system of rehabilitation and reintegration for children and youth in the state institutional, criminal, and judicial systems, with utmost respect for child/human rights.

fields.name: CWY National Websites
fields.description: Alongside the print identity, we created the online templates for the Connect With Yale series that took place across the country. Each city-specific event had its own contained web presence with customized graphics and colors, but also followed a universally cohesive design format.

fields.name: Connect New York Websites
fields.description: We custom designed each of these identity-group focused websites, that corresponded to specific events that targeted Yale's Asian, Black, Latino/a, and LGBTQ alumni based in New York City.

fields.name: Day of Service Website
fields.description: Nymdesign created the visual identity for the Global and Local Day of Service websites. These corresponded closely to the print identity as well.

fields.name: The Redpath Seminar Website
fields.description: For the past five years, we have designed the print and web presence for The Redpath Seminar, and educational outreach program that focuses on such varied themes as environmentalism, political strategy, and emerging superpowers.

fields.name: Yale Career Network
fields.description: Nymdesign worked closely with the Association of Yale Alumni to develop the design framework for Yale Career Nework (YaleCN). This database allows all alumni to input their information; and to search, browse, and connect with thousands of other alumni across the globe.

fields.name: Yale Educational Travel
fields.description: We have designed the templates for this travel website, as well as its service-oriented subsidiary.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Beinecke Rare Book & Manuscript Library Website
fields.description: We determined the site architecture and conceptual design for the Beinecke's online presence. We worked closely with a group of librarians to create a navigational tree element, as well as colors and images appropriate to each section of the website.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Fleur de Sel ID
fields.description: We designed the visual identity for Fleur de Sel, a Michelin-starred restaurant in New York's Flatiron district. While our collaborator UM Projects re-conceptualized the interior space, we redefined the existing identity of custom artwork by infusing it with a modern design sensibility that could be applied across all media.

fields.name: First Fruits Eatery
fields.description: We worked on the conceptual and visual identity of a organic fast-food venture. Working closely with the founders, we created a breadth of items ranging from initial moodboards to refined presentations for investors.\r\n\r\nCreated with UM.

fields.name: F&F ID
fields.description: We design the logo and distribution materials for Foundations and Futures, a conference geared towards connecting Asian and Asian-Americans. This was followed by a full program brochure and website.

fields.name: Bright Eyes ID
fields.description: We designed a clean, simple, and legible logo for this New York-based high-end optometry shop. The logo needed to be visible to potential clients from the street (for walk-ins) as well as appeal to those already using its services.

fields.name: Elias Arts ID
fields.description: Nymdesign worked on the branding project for Elias Arts, a successful music and sound design company. These identity explorations were done keeping in mind an existing system of design that had branded the company for many years.

fields.name: MACA ID
fields.description: We created a unique identity system for the Massachusetts Children's Alliance, based in Boston. It is a state-wide alliance that promotes an integrated, multidisciplinary team response to child abuse. The challenge was to create a visual system that was hopeful and inspiring, but yet also had some seriousness about it.

fields.name: Shubrah
fields.description: Shubrah, an eco-friendly Asian-fusion fashion label, hired us to do a visual audit on existing brands in the market. Based on this research, we ultimately created a series of logotypes for the main Shubrah brand as well as three sub-brands that were infused with rich (Indian) colors combined with modern, elegant typograhy.

fields.name: SoundFest
fields.description: The Asian American Arts Alliance in New York sponsored a festival focusing on Asian-Americans in music. Nymdesign custom-designed a logo for Soundfest, that could encompass the ideology and freshness of this new program.

fields.name: UM ID
fields.description: We have collaborated since UM's inception on all identity materials ranging from the visual logo to stationery, and other print items.

fields.name: Under The Mango Tree
fields.description: Under The Mango Tree, and organic and sustainable food venture based in Mumbai, approached us to create a visual system for their products, website, and other materials. We created a logo that encompasses the concept of growth through use of a clean patterning and bright colors.

fields.name: Bollingen Web
fields.description: In addition to the print identity, we designed an interactive web version of the Bollingen Prize Poetry winners from 1949 till present. This website contains bios of each winner, along with an option to sort them by year or name. Each decade is identified by color variations and each poet by customized images/photos.

fields.name: Cultural Connections
fields.description: We designed the website for Cultural Connections at Yale University. The program has been designed to introduce incoming students to the "diversity" culture. The emphasis of this program is on the experiences of those that are traditionally under-represented, and of issues related to racial and mixed identity.

fields.name: Desipina & Company Web
fields.description: In parallel to the print work we have done for Desipina, we have also designed their website presence.

fields.name: E&E Haute Couture
fields.description: We worked with the founders of E&E to create design that would showcase their innovative product line and highlight the collection. The grey colors of the site structure contrast with the uniqueness and whimsy of each product.

fields.name: EA Web
fields.description: We worked on the website for Elias Arts, a music and sound design company based in New York and Los Angeles. This Flash site was designed to have music and movement as the user moved from section to section.

fields.name: Faber Birren
fields.description: We designed a website for a specific collection dedicated to the study of color.

fields.name: Fleur de Sel Web
fields.description: Alongside Fleur de Sel's logo and print identity, we also designed their website that contained updated menu's and a front page that featured a series of rotating artwork.

fields.name: Green Kettle
fields.description: We designed the web presence for an innovative organization, Green Kettle Foundation, based in Mumbai. There goal is bring about greater corporate social responsibility by providing the tools to create this change. Their clients have included ICICI, Unilever, and UNICEF, among others. The design needed to convey a fresh and clean feeling, but also be serious and responsible at the same time.

fields.name: Hiding Divya
fields.description: We created the online presence for Hiding Divya, a film focusing on depression within the South Asian community. This feature film debut provides a rare, realistic and poignant glimpse into the lives of three generations of women, and how this disease affects all of them. This film was first previewed at the IAAC Film Festival in New York City, and then went abroad to the UK.

fields.name: Unlocking Historical Audio Collections
fields.description: Commissioned by the New York Public Library, along with Yale and Stanford, this website was designed to bring historical sound recordings to the larger public. The album cover visuals are used to enhance the experience of listening to the rare or previously inaccessible recordings.

fields.name: Harvard Kennedy School Web
fields.description: We have created numerous web designs for specific programs within Harvard's Kennedy School. Our clients have included the Corporate Social Responsibility Initiative, Regulatory Policy Program, Consortium for Energy Policy Research, and Environmental Policy Program, among others.

fields.name: JFK Ash Center
fields.description: We have collaborated with the Ash Center for Democratic Governance & Innovation at Harvard's Kennedy School to redesign their existing website. The new design addressed the need for customized mini-sites within the larger container of the Ash Institute.

fields.name: Jules et Jim
fields.description: We created the design for this interactive French language learning tool, based on the classic film Jules et Jim. This included designing the functionality and movement between scenes, written language, and sound.\r\n\r\nCreated with Ahdesign.

fields.name: Let It Resound
fields.description: Let It Resound explores African American sheet music from the 1830's to 1970's. It contains visuals of seminal pieces from the minstrelsy, spiritual, ragtime, musical theater, blues, jazz, R&B, and soul genres. Color, imagery, and texts were used in the design to identify the different music movements as well as related artists/songwriters/musicians.

fields.name: MACA Web
fields.description: In conjunction with the identity/printstuff for the Massachusetts Children's Alliance, we have also worked on their website presence. This organization is committed to strengthening collaboration and fostering systemic and societal change to protect children against sexual and emotional abuse. Through the use of vibrant emotional graphics and colors, we wanted the website to communicate the hope and change that the organization strives towards.

fields.name: MSSA / Nathan Hale
fields.description: We designed a template to be used for online exhibits for Manuscripts and Archives at Sterling Memorial Library. We also visualized their main web presence as well.

fields.name: Ori Goldberg Jewelers
fields.description: We have worked in collaboration with this jewelry designer to showcase his innovative products on-line.

fields.name: Primary Sources
fields.description: The Primary Sources project resulted in a collaborative website, that is used as an umbrella portal to bring together many disparate entities. The design needed to reflect the diversity of the imagery available, but present it in a cohesive visual manner.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Savvy Biz Owner
fields.description: We designed this site to communicate the various options offered by this New York City professional business coach.

fields.name: For People & Places
fields.description: For People and Places: The Work of David M. Schwarz Architects is a virtual exhibition curated by Dean Sakamoto that showcases thirty of the firm's projects that have significantly contributed to the American landscape over the past three decades. The exhibition is presented with the support of the National Building Museum and the Institute of Classical Architecture & Classical America, among others.\r\n\r\nCreated with Ahdesign.

fields.name: Shubrah Web
fields.description: Shubrah is a modern, East-West fusion fashion line that retails almost exclusively through the web sphere. The goal of the website was to create a design that would be fresh and innovative; and could be flexible enough to be adapted to changing seasons and product lines.

fields.name: Sid Espinosa for City Council
fields.description: We worked closely with Vice-Mayor of Palo Alto, Sid Espinosa, during his political campaign for City Council. The website was designed to be dynamically updated with photos, news, events through the course of the campaign. We also designed the masthead/logo that was used successfully in print outreach as well.

fields.name: UM Web
fields.description: We have designed and maintained the website for this innovative, modern, and unique furniture studio for a number of years.

fields.name: UNFPA Imagine Web
fields.description: We designed this mini-site for the United Nations Population Fund to correspond to a brochure that focused on "imagining" futures for global youth.

fields.name: UNFPA CST Web
fields.description: We designed templates to be used globally across all of the United Nations Population Fund regional CST field offices. The templates were designed to have consistent formats, but could be customized through use of colors and image options.

fields.name: UTMT Web
fields.description: We worked closely with the founder of Under The Mango Tree to create a web portal for this ethical, eco-friendly and socially-conscious enterprise. UTMT provides long-term market linkages between rural producers and urban consumers searching for pure, fairly-traded, organic certified agriculture and forest produce in India.

fields.name: William Walton
fields.description: This website, that worked alongside an actual exhibition, allowed visitors to interactively browse through the music of William Walton.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Yale Forestry
fields.description: This website was a portal to bring together lead environmentalists within the field to address the issues of climate change. The goal was to have it serve as a forum space for discussion, invention, and innovation.

fields.name: Digital Collections
fields.description: We designed templates for a digital repository version of Yale's library collections. This site would bring together multiple collections, and also make previously inaccessible collections, accessible.

fields.name: Pickard Chilton Architects
fields.description: This design incorporated drawings, images, and other visual materials to showcase the firm's aspiring portfolio. The verticality of most buildings is enhanced by the narrow columns of the design templates.\r\n\r\nCreated with AHDesign.

fields.name: Francesco & Nicole
fields.description: Invitations for two environmental scientists tying the knot. The invitation needed to capture the meaningfulness of their relationship along with their relationship with nature/earth as well.

fields.name: Bright Eyes Web
fields.description: We built the online identity for Bright Eyes Optometry, a high-end optometry shop in New York.

fields.name: Buy CT Grown
fields.description: This exciting project allowed us to bring local market information to a larger audience. Advanced search information and mapping of various farms, markets, and orchards across the state allow for a quick glance as well as more detailed reading.

fields.name: Edward Stanley Engineers
fields.description: This innovative engineering company wanted to create a website that would reflect the clarity and preciseness of their work, which is all about balance and composition and rethinking materials structurally. The photography was given prominence so that the vitality of the projects could become visible. Created with AHDesign.

fields.name: Neighborhood Music School
fields.description: This school wanted a beautiful yet functional website, where schedules are changing by the seasons and there are multiple events and classes going on year-round. The challenge was create a design that reflected the playfulness of the school (use of sectional color) but also the serious music and dance education that it imparts (clear concise text and sections). Created with AHDesign.

fields.name: MBTA (Boston T)
fields.description: We updated the MBTA.com site to include the "Service Alerts" box for instant updates, and a reworking of information links and graphics across the main page. We also had an opportunity to redesign the MBTA intranet site. We worked on the site architecture, navigation, and homepage content to develop a fresh new look that had clarity of information and easy access to different portals within the T.

fields.name: JFK50
fields.description: We designed the brochure for the JFK50 commemorative event in Washington, D.C. The booklet/program outlined the milestones within Kennedy's presidency through the integration of historic images and quotes, along with the event information.

fields.name: JFK Alumni
fields.description: We have worked closely with the Alumni offices at the Kennedy School to create numerous print materials for specific events.

fields.name: Microsoft
fields.description: Nymdesign has worked closely with Microsoft Silicon Valley's Corporate Citizenship team to create the 2010-2012 Give Campaign materials for the one-month campaign. We have also created other collateral materials for this particular group that include pocketguides, brochures, and tshirts.

fields.name: Saheli
fields.description: Nymdesign worked closely with the South Asian non-profit Saheli to design the materials for their first inaugural fundraiser, Lights On! This included working on the fundraising team for 4 months leading up to the event and creating the logo branding, marketing emails, posters, tickets, and advertisements. For the day of the event, we prepared necessary print banners, silent auction signage and a large-screen interactive presentation.

fields.name: Asian American Cultural Center
fields.description: Nymdesign was commissioned to design 3 timeline panels to commemorate the 30th anniversary of the Asian American Cultural Center at Yale University. This Center is used as a place where Asian & Asian-American students can gather freely, host events, sponsor conferences, and numerous other multicultural activities.

fields.name: Bharatkalai School of Dance
fields.description: We worked closely with the founding director to create a commemorative journal for the 25th anniversary of this Boston-based Indian classical dance school. The piece was designed to have different sections that correspond to states of dance as well as the natural elements, along with teacher/student photography. It allowed the piece to have a structured yet personal interpretation.

fields.name: Fusion Collages
fields.description: A series of 20 fusion collages were created for Arlington Open Studios. The collages combined photography from travels across India with layers of typographic messages and icons. Through these personal east-west explorations, the designer attempted to create a blending of visual imagery that references the in-between spaces of existence. These collages were also exhibited at a fundraising event for the Lexington Educational Foundation.

fields.name: Microsoft EBT/ETR
fields.description: We have worked with the Emerging Business Team at Microsoft Silicon Valley to design a bi-annual trends report focused around following specific industries or trends. The report analyzes different start-ups or established companies that are creating innovative products within a specific field. This information is interspersed with data-driven charts and graphs, and key player interviews. The design was created to be flexible enough from issue to issue, and yet have a unique identity as a stand-alone piece.
